      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I realized this is related to https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/17190 and https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/21199 Ranges, groups and labels are all connected together.\r\n\r\nI see two strong use-cases for descriptors grouping/labels.\r\n\r\nLet's imagine each descriptor group has a title and each member has label. There are two strong usecases for this:\r\n\r\na) BIP44/49/84 accounts, e.g.\r\n\r\n``` js\r\n{\r\n  \"title\": \"Segwit Account #2\",\r\n  \"keys\": [\r\n    { \"title\": \"receiving\", \"key\": \"xpubA/0\"},\r\n    { \"title\": \"change\", \"key\": \"xpubA/1\"},\r\n  ],\r\n  \"descriptors\": [\r\n    \"pkh({receiving}/*)\",\r\n    \"pkh({change}/*)\",\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nb) multisig, e.g.\r\n\r\n``` js\r\n{\r\n  \"title\": \"Corporate Wallet\",\r\n  \"keys\": [\r\n    { \"title\": \"Alice\", \"key\": \"xpubA/0\"},\r\n    { \"title\": \"Bob\", \"key\": \"xpubB/0\"},\r\n    { \"title\": \"Carol\", \"key\": \"xpubC/0\"},\r\n  ],\r\n  \"descriptors\": [\r\n    \"wsh(multi(2,{Alice},{Bob},{Carol}))\",\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf we had a standard that defines this, we would solve the need for labels and ranges at once.",
